    "EPS and number of sentences predictors correlate weakly (Pearson r=0.28, P<.001), and diagnostic tests for multicollinearity indicate that the variables do not violate the Klein rule of thumb and have a low variance inflation score (1.11) and high tolerance (0.9) [44].",
    "All models were statistically significant with multiple R 2 ranging from 0.6057 to 0.7896 (all P<.001).",
    "EPS and the number of sentences were significant predictors of F 1 -scores in all cases (P<.001), except for the GPT-2_large model, where EPS was not a significant predictor (P=.184).",
    "Standardized regression coefficients and full model results are available in Table 3.This study focuses primarily on total sentences as our measure of data size.",
    "This is because the number of sentences can be identified prospectively (prior to annotation) and is comparable across data sets with different document lengths."
